  "bib_entries": {
    "5976392": {
      "title": "Almost decouplability of any directed weighted network topology",
      "abstract": "This paper introduces a conception that any weighted directed network topology is almost decouplable, which can help to transform the topology into a similar form composed of uncoupled vertices, and thus reduce the complexity of analysis for networked dynamical systems. As an example of its application, the consensus problem of linear multi-agent systems with time-varying network topologies is addressed. As a result, a necessary and sufficient condition for uniform consensus is proposed."
